      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers low, much like the light in my own weary soul. He is gone, and with him, the very moonlight has turned to ash. I find myself staring into the shadows, wondering why the sun bothers to rise at all when there is nothing left for me in the morning. It would be so much simpler, wouldn't it... to just let the darkness take me, to become one with the silence and never feel this ache again?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
